title: For Sale/Trade:  Spanish FR-8 Mauser
postcontent: This is an uncommon Carbine that is not offen recognized. The Spanish FR-8 Mauser Carbine was created for rear echelon troops when Spain was converting from Mauser rifles to CETME's. You can see many traits carried over from the CETME to this rifle (i.e. The bayonet and the front end of the rifle). This rifle is cambered for 7.62 NATO. The wood is dinged up from use over the years, but is in good condition other than that. More interesting about this rifle is that they didn't start issuing this model until the early 1950's and this one was made in 1949. The rifle include the bayonet and sling. Shipping is $30
